    <div id="artwork-details">
    <div id="tombstone">

    <p>    Vargi Arsenovich Aivazian<br />
(Born 1908; died 1950)<br />
Dem'ian Bednyi<br />
(Born Gubovka, 1883; died Moscow, 1945)<br />
    </p>
    <h3><em>German "Concern": Only Idiots Accept It. An Old Fairy Tale in the Fascist Style.</em>, TASS No. 0746, June 28, 1943</h3>

    <p>
    Stencil<br />    2220 x 1116 mm<br />    The Kraut crooned sweetly before his underlings:<br />
“Meine Kinder, I want you all to grow fat.<br />
Treating you like superman<br />
I’ll split the harvest with you paternally.<br />
I’ll keep for myself mere trifles, the bottoms,<br />
And give you all the tops.<br />
<br />
The kinder caressed the junk, the tops,<br />
Looking at “Daddy” with fear and hunger,<br />
While “Daddy” with his raging German mug<br />
Filled his belly with an enormous turnip.<br />
<br />
“Ah,” the “kids” sniffed, “listen up Daddy.<br />
Let’s eat the second harvest up differently:<br />
You eat the tops,<br />
And give us the bottoms.”<br />
<br />
“Sehr gut!” the German answered with his usual falsehood.<br />
Sowing the field with stolen rye<br />
He divided the harvest for the German bellies<br />
And took all the tops.<br />
The “kids” sniffed and choked<br />
On the brittle, inedible, dry straw.<br />
<br />
“Had your fill?” the Kraut asked his underlings<br />
After filling his belly, “it’s time to get to work.<br />
Forward march to the front! Instantly!<br />
Or else I’ll totally destroy you all!<br />
The shining band of underlings howl<br />
And march to the front without much joy.<br />
What can they do if the German commands?<br />
<br />
Have you trusted a German? Then you get what you deserve, you scoundrels!<br />    Ne boltai! Collection, Obj: 205835</p>
        
        <!--<p id="dept-gallery">--><!--<br />-->
         <!--</p>-->
    </p>
    </div><!--/tombstone-->

